cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the design of network coding for communication services, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). It also discusses the information theoretical and algebraic views of network coding, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes the integration of network coding with network function virtualization (NFV), which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the optimization of network coding for energy efficiency, which falls under the category of architecture (cs.AR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
